✅ The Sentence You Must Add to Use Bootstrap
Place this inside the <head> section of your HTML file:


<link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
***This line activates Bootstrap on your page — so now you can use any of its built-in classes (functions/styles).***

✅ Some Useful Bootstrap "Functions" (Classes)
These are not functions like in JavaScript — they are CSS classes that do specific things when you apply them.

🧱 Layout & Spacing
container → centers your content with margins

row / col → for grids

py-5 → padding (top & bottom)

mt-4 → margin-top

mb-3 → margin-bottom

🎨 Text & Colors
text-center → center your text

text-start / text-end → align left/right

text-primary → blue text

text-dark → dark gray text

text-white → white text

🧰 Backgrounds
bg-light → light background

bg-dark → dark background

bg-warning → yellow background

bg-danger → red background

🔘 Buttons

<button class="btn btn-primary">Click Me</button>
<button class="btn btn-danger">Delete</button>
📝 Typography
display-1, display-2 → big headline styles

lead → larger paragraph font

✅ Example (You Can Use in Your Page)

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Capsian Civilization</title>
  <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
<body class="bg-light">

  <div class="container py-5">
    <h1 class="text-center text-dark">The Capsian Civilization</h1>
    <p class="lead mt-4">
      The Capsian people lived in Tunisia thousands of years ago. They hunted, gathered, and began shaping early human culture.
    </p>
  </div>

</body>
</html>
